§IL Reae Silviae: dat. governed by adimi& L. S. ξ 423 S. G. ξ 292, Obs. 2. The Vesta] virgins were (in historic times at Rome) six young girls ot good birth who took a vow of maidenhood for thirty years, and devoted themselves to the service of the goddess Vesta. Their position gave them many privileges, hence it was “ a show of honour ” to make Rea Silvia one of their number. Their chief duty was the maintenance of the sacred fire of Vesta, which was never allowed to fail. They had a special house, known as the Reqia, on the slope of the Palatine Hill. Numa is said to have established them at Rome, xx. 3.
